<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 03 at 3:13AM CDT  by NWS Midland-Odessa</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHERN BORDEN COUNTY THROUGH
400 AM CDT...
At 313 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Gail, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Gail.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
